On March 3, famed archeologist Douglas Price will be presenting on the results of his year-long excavation of ancient burial sites in Egypt. The presentation will be held at the Brixton Public Library beginning at 6:00 P.M.

These precious items were retrieved by Mr. Price during his expedition to Egypt, and they are truly one of a kind. They are believed to have been used for farming by ancient Egyptian people.

question.text:
Lichtenberg Air

September 24
To our passengers:

Beginning October 1, Lichtenberg Air will ask passengers to pay an extra 20 percent in baggage fees. As you know, the reason for this increase is because of the rising fuel costs. We regret that the baggage fees have to be increased.
However, passengers are still allowed to have one carry-on bag free of charge. We would also like to emphasize that this has been the first increase in baggage fees for Lichtenberg Air in ten years.
As always, our goal is to provide safe and reliable transportation at a reasonable price. As the price of fuel lowers, we expect to eliminate the fee increase.
We thank you for choosing Lichtenberg Air.

As you know, the reason for this increase is because of the rising fuel costs. Sincerely,
